        <h2>Why Australians Are Turning to Online Therapy</h2>
        <p>The Australian mental health system has a waitlist problem. Bulk-billed psychology sessions are increasingly hard to find. Private in-person therapy costs $150-280 per session — often out of reach for the people who need it most.</p>
        <p>Online therapy platforms have stepped into that gap. But which ones actually work in Australia? Which have real Australian therapists? Which are worth your money?</p>
        <p>We tested and reviewed the major platforms. Here's what we found.</p>

        <h2>Top 7 Online Therapy Platforms in Australia</h2>

        <h3>1. BetterHelp — Best Overall</h3>
        <p><strong>Rating: 4.6/5</strong></p>
        <p>BetterHelp is the largest online therapy platform in the world, and it's fully operational in Australia. You get matched with a licensed Australian therapist within 48 hours. Messaging is unlimited. Video sessions are available on higher-tier plans.</p>
        <p><strong>Pros:</strong> Largest network of Australian therapists; Unlimited messaging on all plans; Easy to switch therapists; 40% recurring affiliate commission</p>
        <p><strong>Cons:</strong> Premium pricing at the higher tiers; No Medicare or health fund rebates</p>
        <p><strong>Starting from:</strong> ~$60 AUD/week</p>
        <div class="cta-box">
          <a href="https://partners.betterhelp.com/go/referral/carevues">👉 Start with BetterHelp →</a>
        </div>

        <h3>2. Talkspace — Best Value for Text-Based Therapy</h3>
        <p><strong>Rating: 4.3/5</strong></p>
        <p>Talkspace is a solid alternative to BetterHelp, with a reputation for responsive therapists and a slightly lower price point. Australian therapists are available.</p>
        <p><strong>Pros:</strong> Slightly cheaper than BetterHelp; Good therapist responsiveness; Flexible plans</p>
        <p><strong>Cons:</strong> Less therapist choice in Australia; 30-day cookie vs BetterHelp's 90-day</p>
        <p><strong>Starting from:</strong> ~$49 AUD/week</p>

        <h3>3. Reclaim — Australian-Owned</h3>
        <p><strong>Rating: 4.1/5</strong></p>
        <p>Reclaim is one of the few Australian-owned and operated online therapy platforms. It was founded by Australians who wanted a service designed specifically for the Australian context — including Medicare and NDIS pathways.</p>
        <p><strong>Pros:</strong> Australian-specific; Medicare & NDIS pathways available; Local support team</p>
        <p><strong>Cons:</strong> Smaller therapist network; No affiliate program</p>
        <p><strong>Starting from:</strong> ~$89 AUD/session (package deals available)</p>

        <h3>4. Mental Health Online — Best Free Option</h3>
        <p><strong>Rating: 3.8/5</strong></p>
        <p>Mental Health Online is a not-for-profit providing low-cost and free mental health support to Australians. It's not a full replacement for therapy.</p>
        <p><strong>Cost:</strong> Free to low-cost</p>

        <h3>5. OntheLine — Best for Youth</h3>
        <p><strong>Rating: 4.0/5</strong></p>
        <p>OntheLine is specifically designed for young Australians aged 15-25. It offers free text-based counselling.</p>
        <p><strong>Cost:</strong> Free</p>

        <h2>How We Ranked These Platforms</h2>
        <p>We evaluated each platform on:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Therapist quality</strong> — licensing, Australian experience, responsiveness</li>
          <li><strong>Availability</strong> — how fast you can get matched</li>
          <li><strong>Price</strong> — value for money against Australian private therapy costs</li>
          <li><strong>Features</strong> — messaging, video, flexibility</li>
          <li><strong>Real user reviews</strong> from Trustpilot and ProductReview.com.au</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>What to Look for in an Online Therapy Platform</h2>
        <p>Before choosing, consider:</p>
        <ol>
          <li><strong>Your budget</strong> — BetterHelp starts at ~$60/week. That's $240/month — cheaper than 2 in-person sessions.</li>
          <li><strong>Your communication preference</strong> — Do you prefer text? Video? A mix?</li>
          <li><strong>Urgency</strong> — Most platforms match you within 24-72 hours. None are for crises.</li>
          <li><strong>Therapist switching</strong> — BetterHelp lets you switch freely.</li>
        </ol>

        <h2>Our Recommendation</h2>
        <p>If you're looking for the best balance of <strong>therapist quality, availability, and value</strong> in Australia — <strong>BetterHelp</strong> is our top pick.</p>

